1
00:00:09,838 --> 00:00:12,773
<i>Last week on Wild Palms:</i>

2
00:00:12,941 --> 00:00:15,569
I want you to set up an exchange.

3
00:00:15,744 --> 00:00:17,439
The chip for Deirdre.

4
00:00:18,446 --> 00:00:21,279
He killed Grace.
He's got my daughter.

5
00:00:21,616 --> 00:00:24,084
You've got to tell the senator
about the Go-chip.

6
00:00:25,287 --> 00:00:27,152
One day, I'll put out the sun...

7
00:00:27,322 --> 00:00:30,223
...and make bare
every womb there ever was.

8
00:00:30,392 --> 00:00:31,882
You wanna be a samurai, Harry?

9
00:00:32,060 --> 00:00:33,220
Now's your chance.

10
00:00:33,395 --> 00:00:35,056
I want you to put this on live feed.

11
00:00:37,699 --> 00:00:39,894
Turn it off!

12
00:01:57,545 --> 00:01:59,172
This is for Grace Wyckoff!

13
00:02:07,922 --> 00:02:09,549
Come on! Move it!

14
00:02:24,172 --> 00:02:26,902
<i>Our fearful trip is done</i>

15
00:02:27,075 --> 00:02:30,101
<i>The ship has weather'd every rack</i>

16
00:02:30,278 --> 00:02:33,543
<i>The prize we sought is won</i>

17
00:02:37,786 --> 00:02:40,550
I'd like to acknowledge the efforts
of one among us.

18
00:02:41,456 --> 00:02:43,390
Harry Wyckoff.

19
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:52,158
How does it feel
to be a leader, Harry?

20
00:02:53,068 --> 00:02:55,161
<i>Viva Zapata.</i>

21
00:02:57,372 --> 00:02:59,670
You wanna know how I really feel?

22
00:03:00,575 --> 00:03:02,167
Sick.

23
00:03:03,044 --> 00:03:04,807
Violated.

24
00:03:06,381 --> 00:03:09,316
Like I killed Grace a second time
on television.

25
00:03:09,484 --> 00:03:11,884
It got results.

26
00:03:13,588 --> 00:03:18,582
<i>Eli, they should have moved you right
from the Perceptory to Channel 3.</i>

27
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:21,661
You would've made a hell
of a programmer, you know that?

28
00:03:21,896 --> 00:03:24,763
It was a terrible thing, Harry,
but it opened people's eyes.

29
00:03:24,933 --> 00:03:26,298
Grace would have demanded that.

30
00:03:26,468 --> 00:03:28,197
Don't tell me what Grace
would've demanded.

31
00:03:28,369 --> 00:03:29,927
You don't know anything about her.

32
00:03:30,105 --> 00:03:32,903
- What do you want from me?
- Deirdre.

33
00:03:33,975 --> 00:03:37,934
Kreutzer said he would give her back
if we gave him the Go-chip.

34
00:03:38,113 --> 00:03:40,911
- I can't do that, Harry.
- Why?

35
00:03:41,082 --> 00:03:43,550
Because with the chip,
he'll be immortal.

36
00:03:43,718 --> 00:03:47,119
A holographic vampire,
unstoppable from some unspeakable...

37
00:03:47,288 --> 00:03:50,155
...unreachable place.
He'll organize the death of the world.

38
00:03:50,325 --> 00:03:51,622
You're as crazy as he is!

39
00:03:51,793 --> 00:03:54,956
- Oh, listen to me Harry.
- No, listen to me!

40
00:03:55,130 --> 00:03:57,257
I'm gonna have my family back...

41
00:03:57,432 --> 00:04:01,232
...one way or the other.
Do you understand that, Eli?

42
00:04:03,938 --> 00:04:06,566
And those are my politics!

43
00:04:07,509 --> 00:04:10,171
And you can go to hell.

44
00:04:12,413 --> 00:04:15,405
<i>And then, now I'd like
to say a few words.</i>

45
00:04:15,583 --> 00:04:16,982
<i>Hello</i>

46
00:04:17,152 --> 00:04:18,449
<i>I must be going</i>

47
00:04:18,620 --> 00:04:21,589
<i>I cannot stay
I came to say, I must be going</i>

48
00:04:21,756 --> 00:04:26,216
<i>I'm glad I came, but just the same
I must be going</i>

49
00:04:27,695 --> 00:04:31,062
What is it, doc?
A heart attack or indigestion?

50
00:04:31,232 --> 00:04:33,962
Stress of the last few days.

51
00:04:34,135 --> 00:04:36,160
You're acutely hypertensive.

52
00:04:36,337 --> 00:04:38,100
- I'd like to put you in Cedars.
- No.

53
00:04:38,273 --> 00:04:40,537
- No hospitals.
- I can't force you.

54
00:04:40,708 --> 00:04:41,936
I'm gonna medicate you.

55
00:04:42,110 --> 00:04:45,079
I want you to stay in bed.
No alcohol or Mimezine.

56
00:04:45,246 --> 00:04:49,273
You're no fun. Grindrod.
What about the Go-chip?

57
00:04:49,450 --> 00:04:53,546
If I can get your pressure under control
you've got maybe a week or so.

58
00:04:53,721 --> 00:04:56,451
After that, I can't say
what your body will tolerate.

59
00:04:56,624 --> 00:04:58,182
A week, huh?

60
00:04:58,359 --> 00:05:00,156
Grindrod!

61
00:05:02,997 --> 00:05:05,693
Why haven't you bailed Josie?

62
00:05:06,267 --> 00:05:07,529
We're trying.

63
00:05:07,702 --> 00:05:10,102
My sister? In jail?

64
00:05:10,271 --> 00:05:12,034
What's the matter with you?

65
00:05:12,207 --> 00:05:15,608
Get her out if you have
to break her out!

66
00:05:18,213 --> 00:05:22,479
We'll never contain this, Papa.
It's a fiasco.

67
00:05:22,684 --> 00:05:24,049
Where's the murder tape?

68
00:05:24,219 --> 00:05:25,914
Being treated at the lab.

69
00:05:26,087 --> 00:05:29,056
Even the die-hard New Realists
think Josie's guilty.

70
00:05:29,224 --> 00:05:30,521
They're running scared.

71
00:05:30,692 --> 00:05:34,184
Then straighten them out.

72
00:05:47,342 --> 00:05:50,971
<i>You knew Harry was going to bust
into Channel 3, didn't you?</i>

73
00:05:51,346 --> 00:05:52,813
No.

74
00:05:55,283 --> 00:05:57,979
You knew he was going
to use that tape.

75
00:05:59,087 --> 00:06:00,987
Why, Paige?

76
00:06:03,258 --> 00:06:07,160
Am I a handsome man?

77
00:06:09,697 --> 00:06:13,565
Am I a virile man?

78
00:06:15,570 --> 00:06:18,596
- Answer me.
- Tony, please.

79
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:21,033
Am I...

80
00:06:22,143 --> 00:06:24,008
...a decrepit cuckold?

81
00:06:24,178 --> 00:06:25,611
Stop it.

82
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:28,840
You were supposed to come back
with the Go-chip.

83
00:06:29,017 --> 00:06:30,882
Instead you brought
a plague to my house.

84
00:06:31,052 --> 00:06:32,986
You're hurting me.

85
00:06:33,621 --> 00:06:35,111
<i>Hello</i>

86
00:06:35,290 --> 00:06:37,520
<i>I must be going</i>

87
00:06:37,825 --> 00:06:42,922
<i>I cannot stay
I came to say I must be going</i>

88
00:06:43,097 --> 00:06:46,498
I'll go back.
I'll get Harry to hand it over.

89
00:06:49,771 --> 00:06:51,261
I assure you...

90
00:06:51,439 --> 00:06:55,773
...I did not come all this way
to die like a trapped wolf!

91
00:06:55,944 --> 00:06:58,538
Like a circus dog!

92
00:06:59,147 --> 00:07:02,605
I am a soldier!

93
00:07:02,784 --> 00:07:06,777
I am mustering my troops...

94
00:07:06,955 --> 00:07:10,948
...and we are storming heaven!

95
00:07:12,293 --> 00:07:14,488
- Why'd you kill her, Josie?
- How'd you make bail?

96
00:07:14,662 --> 00:07:16,926
- I didn't kill anyone.
- There was a doctored tape.

97
00:07:17,098 --> 00:07:19,362
A fabrication.
In a few days we'll prove it.

98
00:07:19,534 --> 00:07:21,161
Is your brother gonna choose
a new running mate?

99
00:07:21,336 --> 00:07:24,271
- Will he drop out of the campaign?
- Absolutely not. Why should he?

100
00:07:24,439 --> 00:07:26,100
- What's your defense?
- Not guilty.

101
00:07:26,274 --> 00:07:28,765
But the whole country saw
you murdered you daughter.

102
00:07:28,943 --> 00:07:30,843
Seeing is believing.

103
00:07:31,012 --> 00:07:32,479
You must be kidding.

104
00:07:32,647 --> 00:07:35,673
- One more question, Josie.
- Will there be a statement from you?

105
00:07:36,250 --> 00:07:37,649
When will the tape be ready?

106
00:07:37,819 --> 00:07:40,083
- Tonight.
- And the Go-chip?

107
00:07:40,254 --> 00:07:42,916
I'm assuming Harry Wyckoff has it
in his possession.

108
00:07:43,091 --> 00:07:44,581
Get word out in the Wilderzone.

109
00:07:44,759 --> 00:07:46,784
If he doesn't turn it over
within 48 hours...

110
00:07:47,328 --> 00:07:48,659
...we'll kill the little girl.

111
00:08:14,555 --> 00:08:17,456
Honey? I'm home!

112
00:08:40,548 --> 00:08:42,675
Coty's room.

113
00:08:43,284 --> 00:08:46,412
I always wanted to see
what his room looked like.

114
00:08:47,255 --> 00:08:48,483
It would have been mine.

115
00:08:49,857 --> 00:08:51,984
Help me out, Peter.

116
00:08:54,796 --> 00:08:58,027
Why did the Fathers take you
from Grace and me?

117
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:01,600
- What do you know?
- They steal children...

118
00:09:01,769 --> 00:09:04,203
...dreams, memories.

119
00:09:04,372 --> 00:09:07,034
A regular fire sale.

120
00:09:07,341 --> 00:09:10,674
When they say, "Everything must go,"
they aren't kidding.

121
00:09:11,646 --> 00:09:13,341
Why me?

122
00:09:13,514 --> 00:09:15,345
Why my family?

123
00:09:15,516 --> 00:09:17,711
You really don't know, do you?

124
00:09:19,454 --> 00:09:21,718
Let's talk to the source.

125
00:09:22,623 --> 00:09:24,181
Wild Palms?

126
00:09:24,358 --> 00:09:26,622
Should we take the car or the pool?

127
00:09:33,234 --> 00:09:37,330
Schenkl. How could I have been
so stupid?

128
00:09:38,506 --> 00:09:40,235
How did they get Josie out?

129
00:09:44,445 --> 00:09:46,242
When are we releasing the tape?

130
00:09:46,547 --> 00:09:49,414
Tomorrow morning.
CNN, all the networks.

131
00:09:49,584 --> 00:09:51,552
<i>Channel 3 will run it
round the clock.</i>

132
00:09:52,587 --> 00:09:55,454
Do you think I should do
a feature during hiatus?

133
00:09:58,593 --> 00:10:01,289
- Deirdre.
- No, wait. Wait.

134
00:10:03,364 --> 00:10:04,763
Hi, sweetie.

135
00:10:05,533 --> 00:10:07,831
Hey, Dad, can we see the tape?

136
00:10:08,669 --> 00:10:11,399
Tabba, take Deirdre to the house.

137
00:10:11,572 --> 00:10:15,440
Come on, little darling.
Tabba is gonna read you a story.

138
00:10:25,953 --> 00:10:27,818
My God.

139
00:10:31,959 --> 00:10:33,984
Please don't hit me, Harry!

140
00:10:34,428 --> 00:10:36,794
You're just like your mother.

141
00:10:36,964 --> 00:10:38,693
Don't look.

142
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:40,528
Don't look.

143
00:10:40,701 --> 00:10:42,601
Get up!

144
00:10:42,803 --> 00:10:44,828
What are you gonna do with me?

145
00:10:45,006 --> 00:10:46,268
The Fathers must be stopped.

146
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:47,964
- And you're one of them.
- No!

147
00:10:48,142 --> 00:10:51,634
I'm just a woman.
But the Fathers are good, Harry.

148
00:10:51,812 --> 00:10:54,542
They want to bring freedom
of images to the people.

149
00:10:54,715 --> 00:10:57,650
As leader of the Friends,
I must set an example.

150
00:10:57,818 --> 00:11:01,276
- You must die.
- No, please, Harry. Don't hurt me.

151
00:11:01,989 --> 00:11:03,547
Long live the Friends.

152
00:11:03,724 --> 00:11:06,488
Death to New Realism.

153
00:11:06,827 --> 00:11:09,819
Long live the revolution.

154
00:11:23,544 --> 00:11:25,774
- The images are no-good.
- Get out of here.

155
00:11:25,947 --> 00:11:28,939
The images don't hold.
You're diluting the images.

156
00:11:30,117 --> 00:11:31,778
- Help you out today?
- No, thanks.

157
00:11:31,953 --> 00:11:34,649
Got some kung fu,
some Johnny Carson.

158
00:11:34,822 --> 00:11:36,790
<i>Some bloopers
from Church Windows.</i>

159
00:11:36,958 --> 00:11:38,550
How about some holotropics?

160
00:11:38,726 --> 00:11:41,160
Fugu just flown in.

161
00:11:41,329 --> 00:11:44,492
- I got some Mimezine, Imagithol-
- Not today.

162
00:11:44,665 --> 00:11:47,964
Say, you're the painter, right?

163
00:11:49,036 --> 00:11:51,300
Sorry to hear about your friend.

164
00:11:51,472 --> 00:11:53,201
Awful what happened.

165
00:11:53,374 --> 00:11:56,104
We're seeing more
and more of that these days.

166
00:11:56,277 --> 00:11:59,804
They call it image sickness.

167
00:12:00,481 --> 00:12:03,382
I don't approve of drug dealers.

168
00:12:03,551 --> 00:12:06,418
I don't even like the way you smell.

169
00:12:06,587 --> 00:12:10,614
- Save your condolences.
- You know, I've been looking for you.

170
00:12:10,791 --> 00:12:15,251
- Get the hell out of my face.
- You've got friends in high places.

171
00:12:18,065 --> 00:12:21,000
They heard about your loss.

172
00:12:21,168 --> 00:12:24,069
They made something for you.

173
00:12:24,705 --> 00:12:27,367
To get you through the night.

174
00:12:27,608 --> 00:12:29,633
It's your friend Tommy.

175
00:12:31,379 --> 00:12:35,110
Come inside. I'll play it for you.

176
00:12:38,753 --> 00:12:41,779
Come on, Twenty-Twenty,
you're gonna like what you see.

177
00:12:48,829 --> 00:12:50,820
Continuing violence
in the wake of today's...

178
00:12:50,998 --> 00:12:53,432
...allegations of doctored holotapes
and conspiracy.

179
00:12:53,601 --> 00:12:56,468
<i>A Channel 3 engineer has been
arrested in the bizarre case...</i>

180
00:12:56,637 --> 00:12:59,663
...and Harry Wyckoff, the disgruntled
head of business affairs...

181
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:03,105
...turned revolutionary, is now being
sought in the murder of his wife.

182
00:13:03,277 --> 00:13:05,541
Only one week ago,
the nation was shocked...

183
00:13:05,713 --> 00:13:08,307
<i>...when Church Windows
was interrupted by a-</i>

184
00:13:08,883 --> 00:13:13,081
- Get up!
- Please don't hit me, Harry.

185
00:13:13,421 --> 00:13:15,946
You're just like your mother.

186
00:13:18,392 --> 00:13:20,792
I'm worried about my brother.

187
00:13:21,395 --> 00:13:23,226
- Emotionally?
- Physically.

188
00:13:23,731 --> 00:13:25,961
I talked to the doctors.

189
00:13:26,133 --> 00:13:29,830
What if his body
rejects the Go-chip, Tobias?

190
00:13:30,004 --> 00:13:32,063
What if it kills him?

191
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:35,341
It's all been
the emperor's new mind?

192
00:13:36,277 --> 00:13:38,643
Never gonna happen.

193
00:13:38,813 --> 00:13:40,678
You know your brother, Josie.

194
00:13:40,848 --> 00:13:43,180
He hasn't come this far
just to let a little thing...

195
00:13:43,351 --> 00:13:45,410
...like the body get in his way.

196
00:13:47,655 --> 00:13:51,022
What will the senator be like
after the transference?

197
00:13:51,192 --> 00:13:52,454
Ghostly.

198
00:13:52,626 --> 00:13:54,753
He'll look like himself?

199
00:13:55,496 --> 00:13:57,657
Like a hologram.

200
00:13:57,832 --> 00:14:01,165
He'll be able to reach
into our dreams.

201
00:14:02,370 --> 00:14:05,396
By then, half the world
will be on Mimezine.

202
00:14:05,573 --> 00:14:06,972
He'll be like Christ.

203
00:14:10,211 --> 00:14:11,735
This better be good.

204
00:14:23,557 --> 00:14:27,220
It's Mr. Wyckoff on the holophone.

205
00:14:40,174 --> 00:14:44,235
Well, well.
If it isn't America's most wanted.

206
00:14:44,412 --> 00:14:47,279
Well, I hope I didn't catch you
at a bad time.

207
00:14:47,882 --> 00:14:49,144
I wanted to tell you...

208
00:14:49,316 --> 00:14:52,149
...you did a hell of a job
on that tape of Grace and me.

209
00:14:52,653 --> 00:14:54,644
I knew you'd appreciate it.

210
00:14:54,822 --> 00:14:56,983
The television programmer in me
was screaming:

211
00:14:57,158 --> 00:14:58,386
"This could be a hit!"

212
00:14:58,559 --> 00:15:00,254
Kill a mystery guest off every week.

213
00:15:00,428 --> 00:15:01,690
Start historically.

214
00:15:01,862 --> 00:15:04,831
One week, kill Caesar.
The next, Hoffa.

215
00:15:04,999 --> 00:15:09,095
"Death to New Realism.
Long live the revolution. "

216
00:15:09,336 --> 00:15:12,772
Who wrote that dialogue? Did you
think someone would believe it?

217
00:15:12,940 --> 00:15:14,305
Does it matter?

218
00:15:14,475 --> 00:15:17,376
We're already climbing again
in the polls.

219
00:15:17,545 --> 00:15:19,012
Don't you get it?

220
00:15:19,180 --> 00:15:20,909
No one gives a damn.

221
00:15:22,383 --> 00:15:25,216
I want my daughter back, Josie.

222
00:15:27,254 --> 00:15:29,381
Does the senator still
wanna make a deal?

223
00:15:29,557 --> 00:15:31,218
- You have it?
- The Go-chip?

224
00:15:31,592 --> 00:15:34,117
- Tell me where to bring it.
- Japantown.

225
00:15:34,295 --> 00:15:36,490
Sunday, 4:00.

226
00:15:36,931 --> 00:15:39,126
The Festival of the Ghosts.

227
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:42,863
Schenkl, you sick animal.

228
00:15:44,405 --> 00:15:45,838
Don't project on me, Harry.

229
00:15:46,006 --> 00:15:47,769
All those years...

230
00:15:47,942 --> 00:15:51,309
You used everything I told you.
How many died?

231
00:15:51,612 --> 00:15:53,443
If I ever get my hands on you,
Schenkl...

232
00:15:53,614 --> 00:15:55,206
...I'm gonna just rip your neck out!

233
00:15:55,382 --> 00:15:58,818
Oh, please, Harry,
stop the adolescent posturing.

234
00:15:58,986 --> 00:16:03,047
Four o'clock, Sunday. Ciao.

235
00:16:14,134 --> 00:16:15,829
What's this?

236
00:16:16,770 --> 00:16:18,465
The Go-chip.

237
00:16:19,139 --> 00:16:22,302
When they took it from your hand,
we embedded it in the coating.

238
00:16:23,577 --> 00:16:26,546
The wedding band
that Josie gave me.

239
00:16:27,081 --> 00:16:30,312
- I like the irony.
- Why now, Eli?

240
00:16:30,484 --> 00:16:31,781
The word on the street is...

241
00:16:31,952 --> 00:16:35,319
...that someone's gonna hit
the senator. Soon.

242
00:16:35,589 --> 00:16:38,752
Tell them I don't want anything
to happen to him until I get Deirdre.

243
00:16:38,926 --> 00:16:42,453
- I can't control that.
- Well, you've got to try.

244
00:16:44,732 --> 00:16:46,131
What's the matter?

245
00:16:49,870 --> 00:16:52,395
- What?
- It's the Mimezine.

246
00:16:52,573 --> 00:16:54,905
Schenkl must have overdosed you
at the Perceptory.

247
00:16:55,075 --> 00:16:58,943
Choko! Now, come on,
I still have some of the antigen.

248
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:07,744
Who is that sitting on my bed?

249
00:17:14,128 --> 00:17:16,460
It feels like you.

